<TEXT>
renewed threats to abortion rights should 
be viewed as a significant opportunity to unify the womens 
movement speakers told the national womens political caucus 
we must bring the same spirit to the fight for abortion rights 
that we brought to the fight for the era equal rights 
amendment eleanor holmes norton a georgetown university law 
professor told the caucus biennial convention on friday 
that means leaving no state unturned it means the same grunt 
work this caucus did in state after state for the era there is no 
shortcut no magic pill no easy way she said 
ironically despite internal and perhaps inevitable 
disagreement over tactics this issue can and will bring greater 
unity 
norton and bella abzug a former democratic congresswoman from 
new york and a founder of the 18yearold caucus said they expect 
abortion will be the issue that prompts young women to join the 
fight for womens rights in numbers not seen since the movements 
peak during the 1970s 
it presents an opportunity to revitalize the movement so it 
may complete the mammoth job that remains to secure women their 
rights and their freedoms said norton former chairwoman of the 
equal employment opportunities commission 
norton said the caucus must not underestimate the need for a 
resilient confident mass movement of broad appeal if we are to 
prevail on the troublesome issue of reproductive choices 
but she added we must avoid the singleissue approach of 
the antichoice crowd when seeking to stop efforts to impose 
abortion restrictions authorized by a recent us supreme court 
decision 
abzug said the threat of abortion restrictions will mobilize the 
nations young people like no issue since the vietnam war 
abortion is the vietnam of this generation for young people 
everywhere 
a womans right to decide whether to have children free from 
intrusion or coercion by government or church or the outright 
violence of any individual is as precious and individual a liberty 
as the right to speak and the right to believe and the right to 
pray abzug said 
without the free exercise of that right she said no woman 
can be deemed to be fully free or equal 
the idea that the unborn fetus is entitled to protection 
from the moment of conception is biologically ignorant and 
philosophically outrageous abzug said no civilized nation can 
be allowed to declare an unborn fetus to be a person under the 
constitution before women are declared to be persons under the 
constitution 
although the number of women holding elective and appointive 
offices has increased during the past two decades the gains have 
been incremental abzug said 
at the rate were going it will take 410 years to get equal 
numbers of men and women in the us congress she said we 
have allowed ourselves to lower our sights and lower our 
demands i believe we have to begin thinking in new ways 
abzug suggested asking both political parties to commit all open 
seats to women until equity is reached in the us house and 
pursuing the idea of having one of each states two us senators 
be a woman 
