<TEXT>
the associated press erroneously reported 
friday that jurors found divorce attorney marvin mitchelson 
innocent in a civil lawsuit filed by a former client who had 
accused him of legal malpractice in her 1984 divorce case 
the verdict was actually a twopart ruling 
jurors found that mitchelson had failed to exercise the care and 
skill ordinarily used by an attorney in such cases but the jury 
refused to assess any damages against mitchelson ruling that his 
failure had not injured his former client 
in a separate finding jurors denied a countersuit filed by 
mitchelson seeking unpaid legal fees for handling the divorce case 
