<TEXT>
a 31 million judgment won by the widow of 
an air force pilot killed in an f16 jet crash in south korea more 
than six years ago has been overturned by a threejudge federal 
appeals court panel 
the widow janet harduvel of lutz can petition the full 11th 
us circuit court of appeals to reconsider the case if the 
request is refused she has said she plans to appeal to the us 
supreme court 
retired us supreme court justice lewis powell served on the 
appellate panel and wrote its opinion released monday 
the judgment was rendered by a us district court jury in april 
1987 against general dynamics the f16 fighter jet contractor on 
the grounds that the plane was defectively designed and 
manufactured 
mrs harduvels attorney howard acosta told the appeals panel 
the plane had a severe electrical malfunction causing the crash 
into a mountain that killed capt ed harduvel in november 1982 
mark dumbroff a washington dcbased attorney representing 
general dynamics asked for a reversal contending the crash was a 
result of pilot error 
the panel rejected the argument that there were defects in the 
designing and building of the air forces newest jet fighter and 
overturned the lower court verdict 
</TEXT>
