arafat but in fact this has become largely arafats congress 
he was speaking outside the first congress held since 1980 by 
fatah the main component of the palestine liberation organization 
most of the 1000 delegates at the conference backed arafat and 
rejected the challenges to his leadership chaath said 
the hardliners have turned out to be less numerous and less 
noisy than some of the top fatah leaders had feared he said 
all substantive discussions of the congress have been held 
behind closed doors the only journalists admitted are palestinians 
who also are fatah delegates 
on its first two days the congress gave its full backing to the 
peace initiative adopted at arafats urging last november by the 
palestine national council chaath and other delegates said 
specifically as reported by delegates and the palestinian news 
agency wafa the congress approved the councils proclamation of an 
independent palestinian state endorsed arafats acceptance of un 
security council resolutions 242 and 338 which guarantee the right 
of all states in the region to live within secure borders and gave 
full support to the 20monthold palestinian uprising 
in an impassioned speech before the congress friday his 60th 
birthday arafat vigorously defended the peace plan and obtained 
fatahs almost unanimous approval delegates said 
the main task of the congress the fifth since the movement was 
founded in kuwait in 1959 is to renew and enlarge membership of 
the central committee of which arafat is chairman 
the panel has been reduced to 10 members by three assassinations 
and two departures of dissidents the central committee is to be 
enlarged to 20 or 21 members 
several hardliners at fridays sessions challenged the 
timeliness and effectiveness of arafats peace moves delegates 
said and the plo leader spoke repeatedly in the debate to defend 
his actions 
wafa reported friday that the congress proved fatah has overcome 
its internal divisions and regained its unity following widespread 
defections in 1983 
the congress has split into political financial and 
organizational committees and is scheduled to close monday but 
delegates said it could well be extended for several days 
</TEXT>
