the savoy the distinctly english dream hotel on sunday marks 
100 years of catering to high society providing an opulent 
discreet and dramatic rendezvous for celebrities magnates 
potentates and royalty 
modeled on the great american hotels of the day the savoy was 
built by impresario richard doyly carte adjoining his savoy 
theater home of the gilbert and sullivan operettas from the 
outset it was a byword for exclusivity 
princess elizabeth later queen elizabeth ii first danced here 
