seem to mix very well together jackson said in an interview 
single rooms go for 140 pounds or 224 a night while a suite 
can cost as much as 520 pounds about 832 
when it opened in 1889 the savoy was a wonder of the victorian 
age with 24hour room service speaking tubes on every floor and 
67 bathrooms at a time when its most luxurious rival the victoria 
had just four 
oscar wilde scorned the builtin washstands saying that if he 
wanted hot water he would ring for it 
all 202 rooms have buttons marked waiter valet and maid the 
hotel still insists on its own custommade mattresses pure linen 
sheets and towels it keeps separate kitchens on all eight floors 
and decorates no two rooms the same using art deco and traditional 
english country styles 
the reservation office keeps 120000 file cards listing the 
needs and idiosyncrasies of regular visitors a staff of 650 
attends to 300 guests who in an average year order 350 pounds of 
